{
  "id": "11-3",
  "title": "Act 3: Final Battle",
  "startNode": "main",
  "nodes": {
    "main": {
      "events": [
        {
          "type": "marker",
          "id": "ch11_act3_start"
        },
        {
          "type": "ui",
          "op": "blackout",
          "args": {
            "enabled": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "ui",
          "op": "fadeIn",
          "ms": 800
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 500
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "dialogue",
          "speaker": "Alea",
          "text": "You three go. I'll hold the rear.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 16
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 700
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "Soren didn't move immediately.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 14
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 300
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "dialogue",
          "speaker": "Soren",
          "text": "Alea——",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 18
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 400
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "dialogue",
          "speaker": "Alea",
          "text": "Think about it. Your three sync rates now. How long can you sustain active combat?",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 18
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 600
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "Soren went silent. He thought about it. He didn't want to speak the conclusion aloud, but he thought about it.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 14
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 600
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "dialogue",
          "speaker": "Alea",
          "text": "Elias's right arm is already non-responsive. Lyra's structural integrity is at critical levels. Your sync rate——",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 18
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 300
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "dialogue",
          "speaker": "Alea",
          "text": "The only thing you can do now is reach the end of this corridor, get far enough to safety, and let your sync rates recover naturally. What you can't do is fight another skirmish in your current condition. You do, and none of you leave.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 18
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 700
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "dialogue",
          "speaker": "Elias",
          "text": "One person alone, you alone can't take them——",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 16
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 400
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "His voice carried something he rarely allowed to show.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 14
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 500
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "dialogue",
          "speaker": "Alea",
          "text": "I'm an adult-class body. Higher sync capacity than you. And I don't need to win. I only need to buy you enough time to get away.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 16
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 1000
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "No one spoke.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 12
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 1000
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "She turned to Lyra. Lyra still held the life nameplate, gripping it so tightly her knuckles showed white. She looked up at Alea, her eyes full of things that had no words, too much, too heavy, all of it stuck there, nothing could come out.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 12
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 800
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "Alea looked at her and then, with barely perceptible motion, gave the slightest nod.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 12
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 600
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "That nod wasn't saying \"it's okay\" or \"don't be sad.\" It was saying something else, something only the two of them had spoken about in that embrace.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 12
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 500
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "It was saying: I know you heard it. I know you'll remember. That's enough.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 10
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 1500
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "Then she turned and walked toward the corridor entrance.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 12
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 600
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "Outside, Solmaris's vanguard was already at the corridor entrance. Scanning lights swept from that direction, leaving cold white streaks on the corridor floor. Alea walked into that light. Her silhouette became clear in it—straight, steady, as she had always been.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 12
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 800
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "dialogue",
          "speaker": "Alea",
          "text": "Go. Now.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 14
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 400
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "Without looking back.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 10
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 1000
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "Soren moved. He pulled Elias along. Elias supported Lyra as the three of them headed deeper into the corridor. Lyra looked back once as she took her first step. She saw Alea standing at the entrance, framed in that light.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 12
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 500
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "That silhouette walked out of the corridor in the next instant, stepping into the gunfire beyond.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 12
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 600
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "The turn in the corridor hid that back from view.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 10
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 1500
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "ambient",
          "text": "Metal striking metal. The discharge of electromagnetic batons. The dull impact of heavy objects colliding.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 12
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 600
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "Alea's voice never came. She didn't cry out, no sound at all. Only the sounds of combat echoed through the corridor, clear, merciless, impossible to pretend not to hear.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 12
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 1000
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "Lyra kept moving forward. Step after step. The life nameplate was in her hand, metal edges pressing into her skin. She held it so tight she could feel its temperature——warmth still lingering from Alea's body, not yet fully faded.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 10
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 800
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "She moved forward. She knew she couldn't stop. She knew that stopping would betray the weight of that goodbye. She knew the choice that walked into the light before her was real, free, entirely her own. She knew all of this, held all of this, and kept walking.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 10
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 1200
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "Light appeared at the corridor's end—a different kind of light, colder, more distant, leading deeper into the safe passage.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 10
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 800
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "The three of them walked toward that light. The sounds behind them faded, fading still.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 10
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 1000
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "Then there was only silence.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 8
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 2500
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "That silence was heavier than any sound.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 8
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 2000
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "Lyra didn't stop walking, but she pressed the life nameplate against her chest, feeling the weight of that metal, feeling the warmth slowly fading from it. She closed her eyes for one step, then opened them and kept going.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 10
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 1500
        },
        {
          "type": "line",
          "layer": "narration",
          "text": "The safe passage door opened ahead. Cold air rushed in. They stepped through, the door closing behind them.",
          "reveal": {
            "mode": "typewriter",
            "cps": 10
          },
          "log": true
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 4000
        },
        {
          "type": "ui",
          "op": "fadeOut",
          "ms": 3000,
          "args": {
            "stay": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "wait",
          "ms": 800
        },
        {
          "type": "end"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  "onComplete": [
    "reward",
    "complete"
  ]
}